commit.message:
workflow: finalize webpack config
- now uses html-webpack plugin to output the final index.html file (this
is served by the express server). to do this, i removed the
`analytics.replace()` and `drift.replace()` from the app.js (i kept it
in the `process.env.RDB_HOST` block, because i wasn't sure if it had to
be there for compatability reasons)
  - this required modifying the gulp `static` task. the task now copies
  the index.html file (the one with `__DRIFT__, __ANALYTICS__`), and
  properly replaces those values and writes it to `static/index.html`
  file. webpack uses `static/index.html`, and outputs the final bundle
  to `dist/index.html`. the gulp task `prod' copies the html file (along
  with the other files webpack generates`) to the `public` folder
- fixed font resolving: for some reason, fonts fail to resolve (even
  though the requests i can find are being pointed to
  `/public/fonts/*`), so i added the `/fonts` path to the express
  server, that points to the `public/fonts` directory
- replace `const` variable declarations with `var`, and other changes to
keep new code consistent with previous code
- remove unecessary commented out webpack configuration

commit.message:
fix: Properly exit process if function `distro_version` fails

`distro_version` contains code that can run `exit`, which is supposed to
exit the whole process. However, `distro_version` runs in a subshell.
By default in Bash, this means that `exit` will only exit the subshell, and set `?`
to that exit code. The rest of script will execute, despite the error.

There are two ways to fix this:
- Enable the POSIX shell option `errexit` for the entire script
- Manually check for non-zero exit code and "cascade the error"

The latter was chosen because it is a localized change that does not
affect the behavior of the entire script.

commit.message:
restructure: Export Redux store from separate file
Defining the Redux store in the same file as the app will create problems
with Vite. There is some issue with circular imports not working
properly with HMR (hot module replacement). Upstream tracks this issue
at vitejs/vite#3033; a workaround is to define and export the Redux
store from a different file. This commit does exactly that to circumvent
the circular import issue.

commit.message:
Improve compatability and correctness of shell code (#16)

* Use a more compatible shebang

OpenBSD, NixOS, and other systems do not have the executable installed
in the same place.

* Improve quoting of arguments

This doesn't change anything in the script now, but will prevent bugs in
the future.

* Improve quoting of paths

Do not assume that pathnames have no whitespace characters. Properly
quote the variables so that word splitting doesn't happen.
